{"type":"message","id":"c86d24e3","parentId":"f1009389","timestamp":"2026-02-17T16:33:58.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is in China and needs to use a VPN to connect to me. They want a simpler way to contact me. Let me think about what options they have:\n\n1. Telegram - already set up, but needs VPN in China\n2. Web chat - there's a built-in web interface\n3. They mentioned they need to use a VPN to connect\n\nActually, wait - the current session IS working. They're talking to me right now via Telegram. So the connection is already working somehow (maybe they have a VPN running?).\n\nLet me check if there's a simpler local interface - like the built-in web chat or something. Actually, looking at the config, there's a webchat channel mentioned in the system message. Let me see what's available.\n\nActually, the simplest might be to just use the web chat interface that's built into OpenClaw. Let me check what ports/interfaces are available.","thinkingSignature":"6b38e67f5fcbcd7dec6fac61925e6966bca32a776da0cadc3af669edd9e96442"},{"type":"text","text":"你现在已经在用 Telegram 跟我聊天了，说明 VPN 是通的呀！👍\n\n还有这些选择：\n\n1. **Web Chat** — 浏览器直接访问 OpenClaw 的 web 界面 (如果开放了的话)\n2. **Telegram** — 你正在用的，已经可以了\n3. **Signal/WhatsApp** — 需要我配置\n\n你现在是用什么方式连上来的？如果 VPN 已经开着，Telegram 就挺简单的了，还有啥不方便的吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":28,"output":277,"cacheRead":7820,"cacheWrite":13064,"totalTokens":21189,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771346027811}}
