{"type":"message","id":"40d59928","parentId":"b3d373f9","timestamp":"2026-02-17T16:52:13.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user gave me what looks like an App Password: savafwq opix qunp fgrfz gfzc abvs\n\nThat's 25 characters - Gmail App Passwords are 16 characters, so this might be formatted with spaces. Let me try without spaces: savafwqopixqunpfgrfzgfzcabvs (that's 24 characters, still not 16)\n\nWait, let me re-read: \"savafwq opix qunp fgrfz gfzc abvs\" - that's 4 groups of 4 letters = 16 letters total. So the password is: savafwqopixqunpfgrfzgfzcabvs\n\nHmm that's still more than 16 characters. Actually Gmail App Passwords are 16 characters. Let me count again:\n- savafwq = 7\n- opix = 4 → 11\n- qunp = 4 → 15\n- fgrfz = 5 → 20\n- gfzc = 4 → 24\n- abvs = 4 → 28\n\nThat's way too many. Maybe the format is different. Actually, App Passwords are typically 16 characters with no spaces. Let me re-examine...\n\n\"savafwq opix qunp fgrfz gfzc abvs\" - if I remove spaces: savafwqopixqunpfgrfzgfzcabvs = 28 chars\n\nWait, maybe it's two words? Let me think about this differently. Maybe the user made a mistake or there's a different format.\n\nActually, let me just try to configure it and see. The user might have given me something else. Let me try setting up msmtp or something to send email, or maybe openclaw has email functionality built in.\n\nLet me check if there's an email plugin or skill available.","thinkingSignature":"3caf1defa4163540386504b2634eaf5fe35fbce1b7947fe562960035e821fc1d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m97y2if03s2i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/ | grep -iE \"mail|email\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":28,"output":425,"cacheRead":7820,"cacheWrite":14565,"totalTokens":22838,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17