{"type":"message","id":"b5f1e15f","parentId":"079fa456","timestamp":"2026-02-17T16:53:15.154Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the password the user gave me: \"savafwq opix qunp fgrfz gfzc abvs\" - let me check if this is correct. I removed the spaces but I'm not sure if that's right. Actually wait - Gmail App Passwords are 16 characters. Let me re-read:\n\nsavafwq opix qunp fgrfz gfzc abvs\n\nThat's:\n- savafwq = 7\n- opix = 4 (total 11)\n- qunp = 4 (total 15)\n- fgrfz = 5 (total 20)\n- gfzc = 4 (total 24)\n- abvs = 4 (total 28)\n\nThat's 28 characters with spaces removed. That's definitely not a standard 16-character App Password. Something's wrong here.\n\nLet me ask the user to double-check the App Password.\n\nActually wait - maybe it's meant to be read differently? Let me try removing spaces and see if it's supposed to be something else. Or maybe the user gave me the wrong password.\n\nLet me try sending a test email first and see what happens. If it fails, we'll know.","thinkingSignature":"f9f5522bed48a65600d3037e8e6dd9f676fa3f19545d16e0b34be0a910fab873"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p3clxzkumily_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"chmod 600 /root/.msmtprc && echo \"Test email from OpenClaw\" | mail -s \"Test\" nohotnnn@gmail.com"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":12107,"output":300,"cacheRead":13483,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25890,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771347187848}}
