{"type":"message","id":"cb58d47c","parentId":"6a58c37e","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:32:22.178Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, there's WhatsApp support! Let me check the docs for how to configure it.","thinkingSignature":"202bcafa903aa09eb113e2140ff5348d72c2217255f0b28a73fe22a97fb3519f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kq09xhz3yrw4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"whatsapp\" /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":168607,"output":71,"cacheRead":13483,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":182161,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771432336265}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6743ac2","parentId":"cb58d47c","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:32:22.207Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kq09xhz3yrw4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/index.md:- [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp) — Most popular; uses Baileys and requires QR pairing.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/pairing.md:Supported channels: `telegram`, `whatsapp`, `signal`, `imessage`, `discord`, `slack`, `feishu`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/pairing.md:  - WhatsApp: [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:- **Session keys** (`agent:alfred:whatsapp:group:120363...` vs `agent:baerbel:whatsapp:group:120363...`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:Session: agent:alfred:whatsapp:group:120363403215116621@g.us\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:Session: agent:baerbel:whatsapp:group:120363403215116621@g.us\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:      \"match\": { \"channel\": \"whatsapp\", \"peer\": { \"kind\": \"group\", \"id\": \"GROUP_A\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:When `channels.whatsapp.groups`, `channels.telegram.groups`, or `channels.imessage.groups` is configured, the keys act as a group allowlist. Use `\"*\"` to allow all groups while still setting default mention behavior.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:  channels: { whatsapp: { groupPolicy: \"disabled\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:Owner is determined by `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom` (or the bot’s self E.164 when unset). Send the command as a standalone message. Other surfaces currently ignore `/activation`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/channel-routing.md:- **Channel**: `whatsapp`, `telegram`, `discord`, `slack`, `signal`, `imessage`, `webchat`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/troubleshooting.md:| Connected but no DM replies     | `openclaw pairing list whatsapp`                    | Approve sender or switch DM policy/allowlist.           |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/troubleshooting.md:Full troubleshooting: [/channels/whatsapp#troubleshooting-quick](/channels/whatsapp#troubleshooting-quick)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/group-messages.md:- Activation modes: `mention` (default) or `always`. `mention` requires a ping (real WhatsApp @-mentions via `mentionedJids`, regex patterns, or the bot’s E.164 anywhere in the text). `always` wakes the agent on every message but it should reply only when it can add meaningful value; otherwise it returns the silent token `NO_REPLY`. Defaults can be set in config (`channels.whatsapp.groups`) and overridden per group via `/activation`. When `channels.whatsapp.groups` is set, it also acts as a group allowlist (include `\"*\"` to allow all).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/group-messages.md:- Group policy: `channels.whatsapp.groupPolicy` controls whether group messages are accepted (`open|disabled|allowlist`). `allowlist` uses `channels.whatsapp.groupAllowFrom` (fallback: explicit `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom`). Default is `allowlist` (blocked until you add senders)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/index.md:- [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp) — Most popular; uses Baileys and requires QR pairing.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/pairing.md:Supported channels: `telegram`, `whatsapp`, `signal`, `imessage`, `discord`, `slack`, `feishu`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/pairing.md:  - WhatsApp: [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:- **Session keys** (`agent:alfred:whatsapp:group:120363...` vs `agent:baerbel:whatsapp:group:120363...`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:Session: agent:alfred:whatsapp:group:120363403215116621@g.us\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:Session: agent:baerbel:whatsapp:group:120363403215116621@g.us\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/broadcast-groups.md:      \"match\": { \"channel\": \"whatsapp\", \"peer\": { \"kind\": \"group\", \"id\": \"GROUP_A\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:When `channels.whatsapp.groups`, `channels.telegram.groups`, or `channels.imessage.groups` is configured, the keys act as a group allowlist. Use `\"*\"` to allow all groups while still setting default mention behavior.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:  channels: { whatsapp: { groupPolicy: \"disabled\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/groups.md:Owner is determined by `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom` (or the bot’s self E.164 when unset). Send the command as a standalone message. Other surfaces currently ignore `/activation`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/channel-routing.md:- **Channel**: `whatsapp`, `telegram`, `discord`, `slack`, `signal`, `imessage`, `webchat`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/troubleshooting.md:| Connected but no DM replies     | `openclaw pairing list whatsapp`                    | Approve sender or switch DM policy/allowlist.           |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/troubleshooting.md:Full troubleshooting: [/channels/whatsapp#troubleshooting-quick](/channels/whatsapp#troubleshooting-quick)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/group-messages.md:- Activation modes: `mention` (default) or `always`. `mention` requires a ping (real WhatsApp @-mentions via `mentionedJids`, regex patterns, or the bot’s E.164 anywhere in the text). `always` wakes the agent on every message but it should reply only when it can add meaningful value; otherwise it returns the silent token `NO_REPLY`. Defaults can be set in config (`channels.whatsapp.groups`) and overridden per group via `/activation`. When `channels.whatsapp.groups` is set, it also acts as a group allowlist (include `\"*\"` to allow all).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/group-messages.md:- Group policy: `channels.whatsapp.groupPolicy` controls whether group messages are accepted (`open|disabled|allowlist`). `allowlist` uses `channels.whatsapp.groupAllowFrom` (fallback: explicit `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom`). Default is `allowlist` (blocked until you add senders).","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771432342193}}
{"type":"message","id":"4bfa875c","parentId":"b6743ac2","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:32:28.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the WhatsApp channel documentation for setup instructions.","thinkingSignature":"8f8443a4792574e5d7f2f0f8f3af2964272b345d6399a1fcfa56fe2ffcfb85f4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y43s7vkiajri_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/whatsapp.md","limit":100}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":169550,"output":63,"cacheRead":13483,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":183096,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771432342207}}
{"type":"message","id":"c89832dc","parentId":"4bfa875c","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:32:28.202Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y43s7vkiajri_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"WhatsApp channel support, access controls, delivery behavior, and operations\"\nread_when:\n  - Working on WhatsApp/web channel behavior or inbox routing\ntitle: \"WhatsApp\"\n---\n\n# WhatsApp (Web channel)\n\nStatus: production-ready via WhatsApp Web (Baileys). Gateway owns linked session(s).\n\n<CardGroup cols={3}>\n  <Card title=\"Pairing\" icon=\"link\" href=\"/channels/pairing\">\n    Default DM policy is pairing for unknown senders.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Channel troubleshooting\" icon=\"wrench\" href=\"/channels/troubleshooting\">\n    Cross-channel diagnostics and repair playbooks.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Gateway configuration\" icon=\"settings\" href=\"/gateway/configuration\">\n    Full channel config patterns and examples.\n  </Card>\n</CardGroup>\n\n## Quick setup\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step title=\"Configure WhatsApp access policy\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      dmPolicy: \"pairing\",\n      allowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n      groupPolicy: \"allowlist\",\n      groupAllowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Link WhatsApp (QR)\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n```\n\n    For a specific account:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account work\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Start the gateway\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Approve first pairing request (if using pairing mode)\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw pairing list whatsapp\nopenclaw pairing approve whatsapp <CODE>\n```\n\n    Pairing requests expire after 1 hour. Pending requests are capped at 3 per channel.\n\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Note>\nOpenClaw recommends running WhatsApp on a separate number when possible. (The channel metadata and onboarding flow are optimized for that setup, but personal-number setups are also supported.)\n</Note>\n\n## Deployment patterns\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Dedicated number (recommended)\">\n    This is the cleanest operational mode:\n\n    - separate WhatsApp identity for OpenClaw\n    - clearer DM allowlists and routing boundaries\n    - lower chance of self-chat confusion\n\n    Minimal policy pattern:\n\n    ```json5\n    {\n      channels: {\n        whatsapp: {\n          dmPolicy: \"allowlist\",\n          allowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n        },\n\n[337 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771432348192}}
{"type":"message","id":"8595040b","parentId":"c89832dc","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:32:36.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so WhatsApp is supported and it uses Baileys. The setup requires:\n1. Configure the channel in openclaw.json\n2. Run `openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp` to get QR code\n3. Scan QR with WhatsApp\n4. Start gateway\n\nLet me provide the user with instructions.","thinkingSignature":"ccb3daaa8c26bdc8237936ee168fc386b7ad2a642714a72b06c2daeb668ff60b"},{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw 支持 WhatsApp！配置步骤：\n\n**1. 先配置 WhatsApp 频道**\n```json\n{\n  \"channels\": {\n    \"whatsapp\": {\n      \"dmPolicy\": \"pairing\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n要我帮你配置吗？配好后运行：\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n```\n\n然后用 WhatsApp 扫码登录即可。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":170171,"output":151,"cacheRead":13483,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":183805,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771432348202}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"150a2b26","parentId":"8595040b","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:33:03.417Z","summary":"## Goal\nMultiple tasks completed in this session:\n1. Configure AI assistant identity (named \"ovo\") and user profile (Boss from Shanghai)\n2. Set up Telegram bot for messaging\n3. Configure Gmail SMTP for sending emails\n4. Compile and send big data developer interview materials to email\n5. Attempt to scrape Hong Kong laws (blocked by anti-scraping measures)\n6. Develop a simple Android parenting score app (app built but crashes on user's Xiaomi phone)\n7. Set up daily A-share stock news email at 9:10 AM\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User is in China, needs VPN to connect to server\n- Preferred communication via Telegram\n- Email: nohotnnn@gmail.com\n- Android app needs to run on Xiaomi phone\n- Daily stock news should include AI, Robot, and hot/trending sectors with TOP 20 news per sector in HTML format with clickable links\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Named AI assistant \"ovo\" and saved identity\n- [x] Configured Telegram bot with token\n- [x] Set up Gmail SMTP (msmtp with app password)\n- [x] Sent big data interview materials to email\n- [x] Built Android app APK (ParentingScore)\n- [x] Set up daily cron job for 9:10 AM stock news\n- [x] Sent test HTML stock news email with sections for Robot, AI, and Hot sectors\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Android app debugging - app crashes on Xiaomi phone, no logs visible\n\n### Blocked\n- Hong Kong laws website (legislation.gov.hk) requires JavaScript, returns HTML instead of PDFs\n- Android app crashes immediately on Xiaomi phone despite multiple debugging attempts (simplified code, added logging, changed themes)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- Used simplified Android code (Activity instead of AppCompatActivity) to debug crash\n- Set cron job to run agentTurn in isolated session to fetch and send daily news\n\n## Next Steps\n1. If user wants to continue debugging Android app, try different debugging approaches or test on emulator\n2. Daily cron job will run at 9:10 AM Shanghai time and send HTML stock news email\n\n## Critical Context\n- Server email credentials: nohotnnn@gmail.com / afwqopixqunpfgrf\n- Android project location: /root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/\n- Built APK: /root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk\n- Daily cron job ID: 31240d42-43aa-4b12-8a55-cdada12782a9\n- Cron schedule: 10 9 * * * (9:10 AM daily)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\n用户反馈当前新闻系统存在两个问题：1）每个板块只有4条新闻，不是TOP 20；2）新闻源只有第一财经一个来源，太单一。需要检查并改进。\n\n## Early Progress\n- 尝试从多个来源获取新闻：东方财富、新浪财经、腾讯财经、和讯网\n- 成功从东方财富API获取到50条/类的新闻\n- 通过关键词过滤AI/机器人相关资讯，获取到28条独特新闻\n- 包含春晚机器人、宇树科技、英伟达、谷歌、特斯拉等话题\n\n## Context for Suffix\n助手正在整理从东方财富获取的28条AI/机器人相关新闻，准备用于展示在TOP 20板块中，同时需要继续扩展更多新闻源。\n\n<modified-files>\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/build.gradle\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/proguard-rules.pro\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/java/com/example/parentingscore/MainActivity.kt\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/drawable/ic_launcher_foreground.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/layout/activity_main.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/mipmap-anydpi-v26/ic_launcher.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/ic_launcher_background.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/build.gradle\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/gradle.properties\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/local.properties\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/settings.gradle\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/a-stock-news-v2.html\n/root/.openclaw/workspace/a-stock-news.md\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"caff6f49","tokensBefore":183805,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":["/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/build.gradle","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/proguard-rules.pro","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/java/com/example/parentingscore/MainActivity.kt","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/drawable/ic_launcher_foreground.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/layout/activity_main.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/mipmap-anydpi-v26/ic_launcher.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/ic_launcher_background.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/build.gradle","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/gradle.properties","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/local.properties","/root/.openclaw/workspace/ParentingScore/settings.gradle","/root/.openclaw/workspace/a-stock-news-v2.html","/root/.openclaw/workspace/a-stock-news.md"]},"fromHook":false}
