{"type":"message","id":"2aa04b6a","parentId":"a4724e63","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:52:38.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the WhatsApp is logged in as \"nohothx\" with ID \"8613429603018:1@s.whatsapp.net\". \n\nBut I need the user's phone number to send a message. Since the WhatsApp channel is configured with pairing mode, I need to wait for the user to send a message first to get their number approved, OR I need to add them to the allowlist.\n\nActually, let me just try to send a message using the message tool and see what happens. The WhatsApp channel might work differently.\n\nActually, looking at the config again, I see it's in \"pairing\" mode, so I can't send a message until the user initiates contact and I approve the pairing.\n\nLet me explain this to the user - they need to send a message first via WhatsApp so I can approve the pairing.","thinkingSignature":"4f7db3318363dd18b9b70dfac174346a1dd2cef4b7826ba07d2a941f1a45ecea"},{"type":"text","text":"WhatsApp 已绑定 ✅\n\n但目前是 **pairing（配对）模式**，需要你先发一条消息给我，我批准后才能互发消息。\n\n请在你的 WhatsApp 上随便发点什么，然后我来批准。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":60102,"output":219,"cacheRead":13486,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73807,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771433551602}}
