{"type":"message","id":"230c70ab","parentId":"aae2f2d3","timestamp":"2026-02-18T16:58:09.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is on Android and can't find the contact. Let me think about how WhatsApp works on Android.\n\nOn Android WhatsApp:\n1. Tap the green chat icon (usually bottom right)\n2. Tap the pencil/message icon to start new chat\n3. Should see a search bar at top\n\nBut they can't find the contact. This might be because:\n1. The WhatsApp account isn't properly linked/active\n2. The contact hasn't synced\n3. They need to wait for the connection to be established\n\nActually, wait - the user might need to first scan a QR code from WhatsApp to link the device. The login command I ran earlier might have created a QR code but we couldn't see it because we're in a non-interactive environment.\n\nLet me try to regenerate the QR code or check what's happening with the WhatsApp connection.","thinkingSignature":"053846ecb242eb43c869a778440219683a1809bcd4fd007faaae89421058598d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_itb7ilsh99uf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":28,"output":216,"cacheRead":7823,"cacheWrite":65690,"totalTokens":73757,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771433870066}}
