{"type":"message","id":"03d42fcc","parentId":"7b132c06","timestamp":"2026-02-18T17:02:44.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config shows WhatsApp is configured with dmPolicy: \"pairing\". The WhatsApp credentials are saved but the service seems to be not running (stopped, disconnected).Let me think about this differently. Since I can't restart the gateway, maybe I can:\n\n1. Try changing the WhatsApp device from the user's phone - make sure it's connected\n2. Or the user needs to wait for the gateway to eventually reconnect\n\nActually, the issue might be simpler - the WhatsApp is linked but not \"running\". In WhatsApp Web terms, this means the phone is not connected to the internet or WhatsApp is not logged in on the phone.\n\nLet me ask the user to make sure WhatsApp is active on their phone and has internet connection. Also, let me check if there's any way to see the connection status.","thinkingSignature":"5723086fc227bb2f4f956fbb86d45547bbf18b4f48a5b351cffbd78209e91281"},{"type":"text","text":"WhatsApp 已绑定但显示\"未连接\"。这可能是因为：\n\n1. **手机端的 WhatsApp 没有联网**\n2. **需要保持手机在线**\n\n请确认：\n- 你的手机 WhatsApp 已登录且联网\n- 手机和电脑在同一网络（或者手机已开启数据）\n\n然后我再试一次：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b6vk8msnhrwa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels status 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":68755,"output":263,"cacheRead":13486,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82504,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771434152264}}
