enclaw\",\"date\":\"2026-02-18T17:02:22.054Z\",\"logLevelId\":3,\"logLevelName\":\"INFO\",\"path\":{\"fullFilePath\":\"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js:2051:46\",\"fileName\":\"entry.js\",\"fileNameWithLine\":\"entry.js:2051\",\"fileColumn\":\"46\",\"fileLine\":\"2051\",\"filePath\":\"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js\",\"filePathWithLine\":\"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js:2051\",\"method\":\"console.log\"}},\"time\":\"2026-02-18T17:02:22.055Z\"}\n{\"0\":\"Gateway reachable.\\n- Telegram default: enabled, configured, running, in:2m ago, out:20m ago, mode:polling, token:config\\n- WhatsApp default: enabled, configured, linked, stopped, disconnected, dm:pairing, error:not linked\\n\\nTip: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli#status adds gateway health probes to status output (requires a reachable gateway).\",\"_meta\":{\"runtime\":\"node\",\"runtimeVersion\":\"22.22.0\",\"hostname\":\"unknown\",\"name\":\"openclaw\",\"date\":\"2026-02-18T17:02:50.376Z\",\"logLevelId\":3,\"logLevelName\":\"INFO\",\"path\":{\"fullFilePath\":\"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js:2051:46\",\"fileName\":\"entry.js\",\"fileNameWithLine\":\"entry.js:2051\",\"fileColumn\":\"46\",\"fileLine\":\"2051\",\"filePath\":\"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js\",\"filePathWithLine\":\"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/entry.js:2051\",\"method\":\"console.log\"}},\"time\":\"2026-02-18T17:02:50.376Z\"}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771434175551}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c42b55f","parentId":"eb90d7c2","timestamp":"2026-02-18T17:03:10.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the logs, I see:\n- \"Waiting for WhatsApp connection...\" - this appears multiple times\n- The WhatsApp is linked (credentials saved) but \"stopped, disconnected\"\n\nThis is a known issue with WhatsApp Web/BAILEYS - the connection depends on the phone being connected. The \"stopped, disconnected\" status means the WhatsApp Web service is not running, which happens when the phone is not connected.\n\nSince the user already scanned the QR code and it's linked, but the gateway wasn't restarted to pick up the connection, it's just showing as linked but not connected. The issue is that:\n\n1. Gateway needs restart after WhatsApp login to start the WhatsApp service\n2. Or the phone needs to be connected for the WhatsApp service to be active\n\nSince I can't restart the gateway, I should inform the user that WhatsApp is bound but needs the gateway to be restarted to work. The user will need to restart the gateway themselves, or we wait for the periodic restart.\n\nActually, looking at this again - maybe the user should try sending a message from their WhatsApp to nohothx. Since we're in pairing mode, they need to message first and then I can approve.","thinkingSignature":"7e3631776d3f897ece6bb8be31788cf54f595a3923364e7e8d09918e89a3dbde"},{"type":"text","text":"WhatsApp 已绑定但网关需要重启才能连接。\n\n**当前状态：**\n- ✅ 凭证已保存\n- ❌ 服务未启动（需要重启网关）\n\n由于我不能重启网关，你可以：\n\n**方法1：你自己重启网关**\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\n**方法2：保持手机 WhatsApp 在线**\n- 确保手机 WhatsApp 登录并联网\n- 尝试从手机发消息给 `nohothx`\n\n你先试试方法2？发条消息试试。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":73050,"output":352,"cacheRead":13486,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86888,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771434175557}}
